# Map the @n3ary scope to GitHub Packages so consumers can
# `npm install @n3ary/neary-gtfs-spec` and friends.
#
# Authentication: the auth token is read from the NPM_TOKEN env var
# (the workflow exports it from the NPM_TOKEN secret). The line
# below uses an unquoted env var so it expands at runtime; the
# `_authToken` field is required by npm.
#
# - In CI: set the NPM_TOKEN secret on this repo
#   (Settings → Secrets → Actions → NPM_TOKEN). The value should
#   be a personal access token (classic or fine-grained) with the
#   `read:packages` scope AND explicit read access to the
#   n3ary/neary-gtfs-spec package, OR a token with org-level
#   `read:packages` permission that grants access to all org
#   packages.
#
# - For local dev, set NPM_TOKEN in your shell environment before
#   running npm install.
#
# - If the token isn't set, npm install will fail with E401. That's
#   the intended signal — the package is private and requires auth.
@n3ary:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${NPM_TOKEN}
